From 2efbab8621c71a919bbdcfefc80eca9e3d6538a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Wed, 28 Jan 2026 13:42:36 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: gxp: fix use of error pointer on syscon lookup failure

When syscon_regmap_lookup_by_phandle() fails, the static i2cg_map
variable retains the error pointer. On subsequent probe calls for other
I2C engines, the check '!i2cg_map' evaluates to false, causing the code
to skip the lookup and use the error pointer directly in
regmap_update_bits().

This results in a kernel panic:
  Unable to handle kernel paging request at virtual address fffffffd
  PC is at regmap_update_bits_base+0xc/0x70
  LR is at gxp_i2c_probe+0x228/0x2b4

Fix by resetting i2cg_map to NULL when the syscon lookup fails,
allowing the lookup to be retried on subsequent probe calls.

Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-gxp.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-gxp.c b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-gxp.c
index 2d117e7e3cb6..bbb16459c74b 100644
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-gxp.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-gxp.c
@@ -515,7 +515,10 @@ static int gxp_i2c_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		i2cg_map = syscon_regmap_lookup_by_phandle(pdev->dev.of_node,
 							   "hpe,sysreg");
 		if (IS_ERR(i2cg_map)) {
-			return dev_err_probe(&pdev->dev, PTR_ERR(i2cg_map),
+			int err = PTR_ERR(i2cg_map);
+
+			i2cg_map = NULL;
+			return dev_err_probe(&pdev->dev, err,
 					     "failed to map i2cg_handle\n");
 		}
 
